column13: Click here to go to the explanatory notes for the Status Indicators

column2:
Guidance Notes:
Please provide updates to the outcome indicators that are applicable to you, and any additional indicators you have been measuring on. Dependent on the reporting period, you will be asked to input actual outcomes or forecasted outcomes (row 17 helps to differentiate this per reporting period).

There is a separate section below (Section C) for reporting footfall data.

Further information on each indicator can be found in the M&E guidance previously issued.

For the Additional Outcome Indicators section, please complete the rows as required. If you require additional rows, please contact us.

Note: It is not required to complete all boxes if, for example, you have not been able to forecast outcomes.  For dates where there is no data, please leave these blank.
You are reporting for the period: 1 October 2022 to 31 March 2023
SECTION A: Confirmation (for completion once section B and C are complete)

Please confirm that you:
- Are happy with all of your project outcomes below; and
- Have evidence to support the data being reported
If no, please explain in the space below:

column16: Please specify if you are able to provide this metric at a higher frequency level than annually

column2: Year on Year monthly % change in footfall

column3: The self-assessment questions do not need to be completed as part of this reporting process

column2: Automatic / manual counts of pedestrians and cyclists (for active travel schemes)
Patronage of the public transport system in the area of interest (for public transport schemes)
Estimated carbon dioxide equivalent reductions as a result of support
Road traffic flows in corridors of interest (for road schemes)
Additional Outcome Indicators - please use the spaces below to tell us about any other outcome indicators that you currently are measuring, or intend to measure.
For additional footfall tables, use the "+" and "-" to expand / collapse the table
